<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>BuildRight Customer Case Study</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #111827; line-height: 1.5; margin: 40px; }
    h1 { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    h2 { font-size: 16px; margin-top: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding-bottom: 4px; }
    p, li { font-size: 12px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>BuildRight AI - Customer Case Study</h1>
  <p><strong>Category:</strong> AI / Construction<br><strong>Customer:</strong> Hennessy Commercial Contractors<br><strong>Stage:</strong> Seed</p>

  <h2>Product</h2>
  <p>BuildRight AI ingests site IoT data, weather feeds, supplier timelines, and project plans to predict delays and cost overruns three to four weeks before they occur.</p>

  <h2>Customer Outcome</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>23% reduction in unplanned delays across four projects.</li>
    <li>Zero churn among the first five paying customers.</li>
    <li>USD 8K MRR within the first three months of commercial use.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Founder</h2>
  <p>Vikram Patel spent 8 years as a general contractor before studying computer science at UIUC. He previously founded and sold a small construction software company.</p>

  <h2>Investor Questions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Can churn and MRR claims be verified with signed contracts?</li>
    <li>What is the model accuracy on projects outside the Midwest?</li>
    <li>How much deployment work is required per new customer?</li>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>
